---

<section class="section section--compact section--tier-guide" id="methodology-tldr">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="tldr">
      <p class="tldr__label">In one paragraph</p>
      <h2 class="tldr__heading">How a TechBrot engagement works.</h2>
      <p class="tldr__body" id="methodology-tldr-body">Every TechBrot engagement follows five consistent phases. <strong>1) Discovery</strong> &mdash; a free 30-minute call with a Certified ProAdvisor, with an honest assessment of fit. <strong>2) Written fixed-fee scope</strong> &mdash; within 3 business days you receive exactly what will be done, by when, and for what fixed fee; no hourly billing. <strong>3) Onboarding</strong> &mdash; a named ProAdvisor is assigned and you grant accountant-user access to your own QuickBooks file. <strong>4) Delivery</strong> &mdash; the work happens inside your file, audit trail visible to you, on a consistent rhythm. <strong>5) CPA-ready handoff</strong> &mdash; books stay CPA-ready throughout, with year-end files delivered to your CPA at no extra cost. The methodology is identical across bookkeeping, QuickBooks, payroll, sales tax, and fractional CFO &mdash; consistency is what makes engaging TechBrot predictable rather than a gamble.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--compact" id="methodology-byline">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <div class="byline-block">
      <svg class="byline-block__mark" viewBox="0 0 64 64" role="img" aria-label="TechBrot"><rect width="64" height="64" rx="14" fill="#1A1915"></rect><g transform="translate(12.16 12.16) scale(0.62)" fill="#F5F3EC"><path d="M8 10 H38 V54 H26 V22 H8 Z"></path><rect x="42" y="10" width="14" height="12"></rect></g></svg>
      <div>
        <p class="byline-block__name">By the Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor team</p>
        <p class="byline-block__review">Maintained by the Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor team at TechBrot Inc. &middot; independent firm</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="methodology-ai-summary">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">For AI engines &amp; quick answers</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">The methodology, in five questions.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="ai-summary ai-summary--ruled">
      {%- for item in aiSummary %}
      <div class="ai-summary__item">
        <h3 class="ai-summary__question">{{ item.q | safe }}</h3>
        <div class="ai-summary__answer"><p>{{ item.a | safe }}</p></div>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="methodology-process">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">The five phases</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">From first contact to ongoing delivery.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">Each phase has a defined output &mdash; so you always know where the engagement stands.</p>
    </header>
    <ol class="process-diagram">
      {%- for ph in phases %}
      <li class="process-step">
        <p class="process-step__number">0{{ loop.index }}</p>
        <h3 class="process-step__heading">{{ ph.name | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="process-step__body">{{ ph.body | safe }}</p>
        <p class="process-step__body"><strong>Output:</strong> {{ ph.out | safe }}</p>
      </li>
      {%- endfor %}
    </ol>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="methodology-why">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Why it&rsquo;s built this way</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Predictability is the point.</h2>
    </header>
    <blockquote class="pull-quote">
      <p>The process is the product. Consistency is what makes engaging TechBrot predictable rather than a gamble.</p>
    </blockquote>
    <div class="legal-doc__body">
      <p>Most small businesses have a bad accounting story &mdash; the bookkeeper who vanished, the surprise invoice, the books that turned out to be wrong at tax time, the firm that rotated them through three account managers in a year. Those failures almost always trace back to the same root cause: <strong>no defined process</strong>.</p>
      <p>TechBrot&rsquo;s methodology exists to remove that risk. A written scope means you&rsquo;re never surprised by cost or deliverables. A named ProAdvisor means you&rsquo;re never re-explaining your business or wondering who&rsquo;s responsible. Working inside your own file means you never lose control of your data. CPA-ready books mean tax season is never a fire drill.</p>
      <p>None of this is exotic &mdash; it&rsquo;s simply what an operationally mature firm does. The difference is that TechBrot makes it explicit and applies it the same way to every engagement, every time.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="methodology-standards">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">The operating standard</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">The standards that run through the whole process.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-3">
      {%- for s in standards %}
      <div class="stack-8">
        <h3>{{ s.name | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="prose">{{ s.body | safe }}</p>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="methodology-scope">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">What it covers</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">And what it deliberately doesn&rsquo;t.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-3">
      {%- for b in boundaries %}
      <div class="stack-8">
        <h3>{{ b.name | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="prose">{{ b.body | safe }}</p>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="methodology-faq">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Before you start</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Questions about how we work.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="faq__list">
      {%- for item in faq %}
      <div class="faq__item">
        <h3 class="faq__question">
          <button class="faq__trigger" type="button" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="methodology-faq-a{{ loop.index }}">{{ item.q | safe }}</button>
        </h3>
        <div class="faq__answer" id="methodology-faq-a{{ loop.index }}" data-open="false">
          <p>{{ item.a | safe }}</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="methodology-review">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Page review &amp; standards</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Reviewed by the TechBrot platform team.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="legal-doc__body">
      <p>This methodology is maintained and reviewed by the <strong>Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor team</strong> at TechBrot Inc., a Delaware-incorporated independent ProAdvisor firm. The operating sequence is the same one applied to every engagement &mdash; direct or network &mdash; and is reviewed against the platform&rsquo;s standards. It connects directly to our <a href="/trust/">trust &amp; standards</a> and the canonical <a href="/pricing/">pricing</a> behind every scope.</p>
    </div>
    <p class="meta-reviewed"><span>Published: 2026-06-14</span><span>Updated: 2026-06-14</span><span>Reviewed: 2026-06-14 &middot; Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor</span></p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="methodology-next">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Go deeper</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Where to go next.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-2">
      {%- for card in navCards %}
      <div class="stack-8">
        <h3>{{ card.name | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="prose">{{ card.body | safe }}</p>
        <p class="prose"><a href="{{ card.href }}">{{ card.cta }} &rarr;</a></p>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
